				<td class="PanelBodyAlternate"><span class="SmallBoldText">Everquest II. To be or not to be.<a name="41604"/></span><br><span class="SmallText"> Posted: </span><span class="SmallText">May 23 04 9:47 PM</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span>Everquest II is coming out in September I think. I am eargerly anticipating its arrival. How many of you share this anxiety to try it out? Will you play if you have to upgrade your computer or buy a new one altogether?
<br />

<br />
The minimum system requirements dont seem to be very steep (512 megs of RAM, 64 megs of video RAM). The problem with this is that if I'm lagging incredibly in bazaar to the point where I have to look at the floor when I walk (512ram,64video), how on earth am I going to be able to play a game like EQII with the same specs? Thank God RAM doesnt cost as much as it did around 1994.
<br />

<br />
How many of you are going to play EQII? How much are you willing to spend ugrading your system if it comes to that?
<br />

<br />
SPECIFIC SYSTEM REQUIREMENTS (from SOE):
<br />
-Operating System: Windows 98/2000/ME/XP 
<br />
-Processor: 1GHz or greater 
<br />
-RAM: 512 MB 
<br />
-Video Card: DirectX 9 compatible. Pixel shader and vertex shader compatible hardware with 64 MB of texture memory 
<br />
-Sound Card: DirectSound compatible audio hardware 
<br />

<br />
</span></td>
