				<td class="PanelBodyAlternate"><span class="SmallBoldText">Re: Will hold off.<a name="42081"/></span><br><span class="SmallText"> Posted: </span><span class="SmallText">May 25 04 12:15 PM</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span>I'm with Klapton, 
<br />

<br />
I'm always surprised by the amount of hostility people have for SoE.  If you don't like their games, why are you reading the boards about them?  It just totally amazes me that people who dislike something so much stilll pay so much attention to what happens.  
<br />

<br />
It'd be like me going to dozens of baseball sites every day just to post how much I dislike baseball...  People are odd.
<br />

<br />
As for me, I'm eagerly awaiting EQ2.  I've played EQ1 for well over 4 years, and have enjoyed it immensely.  I've taken breaks, come back, had wane periods, tried other games, but I've always felt that EQ had WAY more to offer than anything else out there.  The only reason I have ever lost interest is simply because I've done it all too much.  It's not their fault that I played 2.5 hours nearly every day for what, 4 years?  Can't call that a failure.
<br />

<br />
I've been following EQ2 closely and it looks amazing (and not just hte graphics!).  Outstanding graphics to be sure, but it also has huge engine, great story lines, life like AI, and rich environments.  They are really trying to push the genre.  
<br />

<br />
Sony has invested tons of money into the engine, characters, storyline, etc... and I fully expect it to be leagues above every other game out there. 
<br />

<br />
A year from now, I expect most people on these boards will be playing EQ2.
<br />

<br />
Hunt well, and with less bitterness,
<br />
Wyndaria.
